&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="introduction-to-pandas"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;3) Introduction to Pandas&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speaker: Piotr Migdal&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pandas is an open source, BSD-licensed library providing high-performance, easy-to-use data structures and data analysis tools for the Python programming language.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="reference external" href="http://nbviewer.ipython.org/gist/stared/6dc90471f0154c697c8b"&gt;http://nbviewer.ipython.org/gist/stared/6dc90471f0154c697c8b&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Introduction to Pandas, by Piotr Migdal (&lt;a href="https://twitter.com/pmigdal"&gt;@pmigdal&lt;/a&gt;) &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/search?q=%23pybcn&amp;amp;src=hash"&gt;#pybcn&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://t.co/OeVg971Rsx"&gt;pic.twitter.com/OeVg971Rsx&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;— Python Barcelona (@pybcn) &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/pybcn/statuses/459412929951985664"&gt;April 24, 2014&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
