&lt;div class="section" id="pyramid-python-webframework"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;1) Pyramid Python WebFramework&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Speaker: Ramon Navarro Bosch&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pyramid is a small, fast, down-to-earth Python web application development framework. It is developed as part of the Pylons Project.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;iframe src="http://www.slideshare.net/slideshow/embed_code/31686189" width="427" height="356" frameborder="0" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" scrolling="no" style="border:1px solid #CCC; border-width:1px 1px 0; margin-bottom:5px; max-width: 100%;" allowfullscreen&gt; &lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;div style="margin-bottom:5px"&gt; &lt;strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.slideshare.net/bloodbare/pyramid-31686189" title="Pyramid" target="_blank"&gt;Pyramid&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/strong&gt; from &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.slideshare.net/bloodbare" target="_blank"&gt;Ramon Bosch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Pyramid Python WebFramework, by Ramon Navarro (&lt;a href="https://twitter.com/bloodbare"&gt;@bloodbare&lt;/a&gt;) &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/search?q=%23pybcn&amp;amp;src=hash"&gt;#pybcn&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://t.co/lV5hpqOmcE"&gt;pic.twitter.com/lV5hpqOmcE&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;— Python Barcelona (@pybcn) &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/pybcn/statuses/436564028190904320"&gt;February 20, 2014&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="simple-webapps-with-nginx-uwsgi-emperor-bottle"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;2) Simple webapps with nginx + uWSGI emperor + Bottle&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speaker: Jordi Soucheiron&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bottle is a small microframework that lets you build simple python webapps in a few minutes. This talk will explain how to build simple webapp from scratch and configure your system to deploy many other apps concurrently with a rock solid and scalable setup.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;iframe src="http://www.slideshare.net/slideshow/embed_code/31531197" width="427" height="356" frameborder="0" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" scrolling="no" style="border:1px solid #CCC; border-width:1px 1px 0; margin-bottom:5px; max-width: 100%;" allowfullscreen&gt; &lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;div style="margin-bottom:5px"&gt; &lt;strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.slideshare.net/jordixou/python-meetup-31531197" title="Simple webapps with nginx, uwsgi emperor and bottle" target="_blank"&gt;Simple webapps with nginx, uwsgi emperor and bottle&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/strong&gt; from &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.slideshare.net/jordixou" target="_blank"&gt;Jordi Soucheiron&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Simple webapps with nginx + uWSGI emperor + Bottle, by Jordi Soucheiron (&lt;a href="https://twitter.com/jordixou"&gt;@jordixou&lt;/a&gt;) &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/search?q=%23pybcn&amp;amp;src=hash"&gt;#pybcn&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://t.co/RMYniXWsTN"&gt;pic.twitter.com/RMYniXWsTN&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;— Python Barcelona (@pybcn) &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/pybcn/statuses/436570487955918848"&gt;February 20, 2014&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="rapid-web-development-with-web2py"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;3) Rapid web development with Web2py&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speaker: Giorgio Zoppi&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full-stack framework for rapid development of fast, scalable, secure and portable database-driven web-based applications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Rapid web development with Web2py, by Giorgio Zoppi (&lt;a href="https://twitter.com/jo_zoppi"&gt;@jo_zoppi&lt;/a&gt;) &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/search?q=%23pybcn&amp;amp;src=hash"&gt;#pybcn&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://t.co/VWOWkWUJLY"&gt;pic.twitter.com/VWOWkWUJLY&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;— Python Barcelona (@pybcn) &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/pybcn/statuses/436577595820630017"&gt;February 20, 2014&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="pybcn-org-website-powered-by-nikola"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;4) Pybcn.org website powered by Nikola&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Speaker: Areski Belaid&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This talk will introduce Nikola, a static site and blog generator.
Static websites are safer, use fewer resources, and avoid vendor and platform lock-in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;iframe src="http://www.slideshare.net/slideshow/embed_code/31443327" width="427" height="356" frameborder="0" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" scrolling="no" style="border:1px solid #CCC; border-width:1px 1px 0; margin-bottom:5px; max-width: 100%;" allowfullscreen&gt; &lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;div style="margin-bottom:5px"&gt; &lt;strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.slideshare.net/areski/nikola-a-static-blog-site-generator-python-meetup-19-feb2014" title="Nikola, a static blog &amp;amp; site generator python meetup 19 feb2014" target="_blank"&gt;Nikola, a static blog &amp;amp; site generator python meetup 19 feb2014&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/strong&gt; from &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.slideshare.net/areski" target="_blank"&gt;Areski Belaid&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Did you know that the &lt;a href="http://t.co/w3Khlgca3U"&gt;http://t.co/w3Khlgca3U&lt;/a&gt; website powered by Nikola? by Areski Belaid (&lt;a href="https://twitter.com/areskib"&gt;@areskib&lt;/a&gt;) &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/search?q=%23pybcn&amp;amp;src=hash"&gt;#pybcn&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://t.co/Gl9UOLWAQZ"&gt;pic.twitter.com/Gl9UOLWAQZ&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;— Python Barcelona (@pybcn) &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/pybcn/statuses/436581795501719552"&gt;February 20, 2014&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
